<% content_for :head do  %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag "tour.css" %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag "jquery.lightbox-0.5.css" %>
<% end %>

<div id="page-title">

        <h1> Features overview </h1>
        <p>Fleetnext has comprehensive functionality for easy fleet management online.</p>

</div> <!-- /page-title -->


<div id="content">

        <div class="container">

                <div class="row">
                      <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                              <h3> <img src="/assets/allonline.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                              Every vehicle online
                              </h3>
                              <br/>
                              <p>
                              (a) Create a profile for each vehicle in the fleet. Store information such as vehicle make, model, license plate number, ownership details, 
                              engine number, chassis number, fuel type, base location/branch. <br/><br/>
                              (b) Update purchase details such as purchase date, vehicle finance info, invoice number etc.   <br/><br/>
                              (c) Scan and upload any relevant paperwork such as registration certificates, warranty documents, manuals.
                              </p>
                           </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />
                
                
                <div class="row">
                        <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                            <h3> <img src="/assets/alerts.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                            Renew vehicle documents on time
                            </h3>
                            <br/>
                            <p>(a) Simplify the management of vehicle documentation such as insurance certificates,taxes, fitness certificates, permits to ensure statutory compliance. <br/><br/>
                               (b) For each document, keep track of its expiry date, reference number, issuing authority. <br/><br/>
                               (c) Find documents that are due soon or have already expired. <br/><br/>
                               (d) Setup email reminders to alert you when a document is due for renewal.<br/><br/>
                            </p>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />
                
                <div class="row">
                        <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                            <h3> <img src="/assets/repair.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                            Maintain vehicle service history
                            </h3>
                            <br/>
                            <p>
                              (a) Store service records for scheduled vehicle maintenance and emergency repair work. <br/><br/>
                              (b) Store service details such as tasks (labour) completed, parts consumed, service costs, invoice. <br/><br/>
                              (c) Upload any related paperwork such as workorders, invoice etc. <br/><br/>
                            </p>
                          </div>
                        </div>                                  
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />                         
                
                
                <div class="row">
                        <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                            <h3> <img src="/assets/alerts.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                            Stay on top of preventive maintenance
                            </h3>
                            <br/>
                            <p>
                              (a) Setup service reminders both by time (e.g. Change engine oil every 365 days) and by mileage (e.g. Change engine oil every 10000 kms). <br/><br/>
                              (b) Service reminders automatically update when a new vehicle service is logged. <br/><br/>
                              (c) Setup email reminders to alert you when a vehicle is due for service. <br/><br/>
                              (d) Duplicate a vehicle's service reminder schedule and copy it to other vehicles in the fleet. <br/><br/>                              
                            </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />                
                
                
               <div class="row">
                       <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                                <h3> <img src="/assets/tyre.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                                Comprehensive tyre management
                                </h3>
                                <br/>
                                <p>
                                  (a) Track the lifecycle of a tyre from purchase to scrap. <br/> <br/>
                                  (b) Store important tyre attributes such as serial number, make and size.  <br/><br/>
                                  (c) Update tyre positions on vehicle, maintain tyre remold (rethread) history. <br/><br/>
                                  (d) Locate spare tyres. <br/><br/>
                                  (e) Quickly find currently fitted tyres on a vehicle.<br/><br/>
                                </p>
                           </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />

                <div class="row">
                        <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                            <h3> <img src="/assets/fuel.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                            Track fuel consumption
                            </h3>
                            <br/>
                            <p>
                                (a) Add daily fuel purchases (paid by cash, credit or fleetcards) and capture details such as quantity issued, rate and total amount. <br/><br/>
                                (b) Audit fuel transactions by reconciling them against vendor invoices or fleetcard statements.  <br/><br/>
                                (c) Calculate vehicle fuel efficiency and total fuel costs. <br/><br/>
                            </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />  

                <div class="row">
                       <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                                <h3> <img src="/assets/users.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                                Store driver records
                                </h3>
                                <br/>
                                <p>
                                  (a) Store driver profiles with bio-data, address, contact information. <br/><br/>
                                  (b) Update current status for driver leave management.  <br/><br/>                        
                                  (c) Keep records of all driver licenses and expiry dates. Enable email reminders to alert you when a driver license is due for renewal.<br/><br/>
                                  (d) Setup driver training programs (e.g. defensive driving course) and record course completion.<br/><br/>
                                </p>
                           </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />
                
                
                <div class="row">
                        <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                            <h3> <img src="/assets/update.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                            Up-to-date vehicle mileage logs
                            </h3>
                            <br/>
                            <p>
                              (a) Manually update vehicle mileage reading (odometer reading) on a routine basis.  <br/><br/>
                              (b) Units (kilometres and miles) can be configured on per-vehicle basis.   <br/><br/>
                            </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />

                <div class="row">
                       <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                                <h3> <img src="/assets/pdf_icon.png" alt="Fleetnext" />
                                 Generate reports
                                </h3>
                                <br/>
                                <p>
                                  (a) Multiple PDF reports to export vehicle service records, fuel transactions, tyre history and other fleet data. <br/><br/>
                                  (b) Analyze service, fuel and tyre costs including key metrics such as fuel efficiency, service costs per km (or per mile), tyre costs per km (or per mile).  <br/><br/>                                                          
                                </p>
                           </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />                
                

                <div class="row">
                        <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                                 <h3> <img src="/assets/upload.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                                         Backup data
                                 </h3>
                                  <br/>
                                 <p>
                                   (a) Select one or multiple vehicles and download its data (such as vehicle profile, acquisition, disposal, documents, tyres, service history, fuel history, mileage log) to Microsoft excel file . <br/><br/>
                                   (b) At any given point of time, you can take a backup of your entire account and save a local copy on your computer. <br/><br/>
                                 </p>
                           </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                <hr class="row-divider" />

                <div class="row">
                       <div class="grid-8">
                          <div class="service-item">
                          <h3> <img src="/assets/users.jpg" alt="Fleetnext" />
                          Easy user administration
                          </h3>
                          <br/>
                          <p>
                            (a) Fleetnext is a multi-user fleet management platform. <br/><br/>
                            (b) Add and remove users as your organization evolves. <br/><br/>
                            (c) See complete log of user activity.<br/><br/>
                            (d) Each user can be assigned custom permissions for viewing, updating, exporting data across different modules. <br/><br/>
                          </p>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                </div> <!-- /row -->
                
            

                <%= render :partial => "signup" %>

        </div> <!-- /container -->

</div> <!-- /content -->
	
